90
00:03:26,390 --> 00:03:29,260
Story number two, "The Pet Spider."

91
00:03:29,260 --> 00:03:32,250
Once when I was a kid, I
found a spider in my bedroom.

92
00:03:32,250 --> 00:03:35,460
It was a small brown spider,
and I thought it was cute.

93
00:03:35,460 --> 00:03:38,610
It had spun a web up in
the corner of the ceiling

94
00:03:38,610 --> 00:03:40,480
and was sitting in the middle of it.

95
00:03:40,480 --> 00:03:42,660
I got a small jar with a lid from my mom

96
00:03:42,660 --> 00:03:45,680
and I used the lid to flick
the spider off its web

97
00:03:45,680 --> 00:03:49,490
into the jar and then
quickly screwed on the lid.

98
00:03:49,490 --> 00:03:50,870
When my dad came in for lunch,

99
00:03:50,870 --> 00:03:53,380
I showed him the spider
in the jar and he told me

100
00:03:53,380 --> 00:03:56,420
I should find a bigger jar
and put some small holes

101
00:03:56,420 --> 00:03:59,570
in the lid so the spider
would have fresh air.

102
00:03:59,570 --> 00:04:02,240
My mom told me that I should
catch flies in the kitchen

103
00:04:02,240 --> 00:04:04,660
and put them in the jar
for the spider to eat.

104
00:04:04,660 --> 00:04:07,710
I'm not sure if she was excited
that I had a pet spider,

105
00:04:07,710 --> 00:04:09,070
but she was certainly excited

106
00:04:09,070 --> 00:04:12,063
that I would be ridding the
kitchen of flies each day.

107
00:04:13,000 --> 00:04:15,120
I rummaged around in the
cupboard below the sink

108
00:04:15,120 --> 00:04:17,399
and found a large glass jar with a lid.

109
00:04:17,399 --> 00:04:19,479
I went outside and found some stones,

110
00:04:19,480 --> 00:04:21,800
some small sticks and
some blades of grass,

111
00:04:21,800 --> 00:04:23,250
and put them in the jar.

112
00:04:23,250 --> 00:04:26,060
I wanted the jar to be nice
and cozy for my spider,

113
00:04:26,060 --> 00:04:27,400
so it would be happy.

114
00:04:27,400 --> 00:04:30,990
And I thought it would like
the stones, sticks and grass.

115
00:04:30,990 --> 00:04:32,970
I asked to borrow my
dad's hammer and a nail

116
00:04:32,970 --> 00:04:34,940
and punched some holes in the lid.

117
00:04:34,940 --> 00:04:37,530
I also filled an old bottle cap with water

118
00:04:37,530 --> 00:04:40,230
and slowly lowered it to
the bottom of the jar,

119
00:04:40,230 --> 00:04:42,380
without spilling any of the water.

120
00:04:42,380 --> 00:04:45,370
I then carefully transferred
the spider from the smaller jar

121
00:04:45,370 --> 00:04:47,683
to the bigger jar and screwed the lid on.

122
00:04:48,720 --> 00:04:51,040
I wasn't sure where to
put the jar in my room.

123
00:04:51,040 --> 00:04:53,610
I didn't know if spiders
liked light or dark,

124
00:04:53,610 --> 00:04:56,440
but seeing the web up in the dark corner,

125
00:04:56,440 --> 00:04:58,600
I assumed they liked the dark.

126
00:04:58,600 --> 00:05:02,470
So I put the jar on my
bookshelf, far from the window.

127
00:05:02,470 --> 00:05:04,020
I named my spider Rick.

128
00:05:04,020 --> 00:05:06,550
And every day I would check
to see if he had spun a web.

129
00:05:06,550 --> 00:05:09,650
I would catch flies and put
them in the jar for Rick to eat.

130
00:05:09,650 --> 00:05:12,860
Unfortunately, Rick
never made a spiderweb,

131
00:05:12,860 --> 00:05:15,630
so he never caught and
ate any of the flies.

132
00:05:15,630 --> 00:05:18,440
When I watched him, he
would just sit in one spot.

133
00:05:18,440 --> 00:05:19,860
I would never see him move.

134
00:05:19,860 --> 00:05:23,260
But he was always in a
different place when I looked,

135
00:05:23,260 --> 00:05:25,033
so I knew he was still alive.

136
00:05:26,030 --> 00:05:27,610
A couple of days after catching Rick,

137
00:05:27,610 --> 00:05:31,060
I went to the library and
borrowed a book about spiders.

138
00:05:31,060 --> 00:05:34,800
In the book it said that
spiders didn't make great pets.

139
00:05:34,800 --> 00:05:38,470
And that the best thing for
them is to be in the wild.

140
00:05:38,470 --> 00:05:40,970
I was sad, but I knew
I had to let Rick go.

141
00:05:40,970 --> 00:05:44,090
I carefully took the lid off
the jar and set it on the floor

142
00:05:44,090 --> 00:05:45,720
in the corner of my room.

143
00:05:45,720 --> 00:05:47,010
A few flies flew out,

144
00:05:47,010 --> 00:05:49,320
but Rick just sat on his favorite stick.

145
00:05:49,320 --> 00:05:50,730
I decided to let him be.

146
00:05:50,730 --> 00:05:52,750
After all, he usually only moved

147
00:05:52,750 --> 00:05:54,800
when no one was watching him.

148
00:05:54,800 --> 00:05:56,270
The next day, Rick was gone.

149
00:05:56,270 --> 00:05:57,660
He never came back.

150
00:05:57,660 --> 00:05:59,970
I thought maybe he would
return in a day or two

151
00:05:59,970 --> 00:06:02,620
to his web in the
ceiling, but he never did.

152
00:06:02,620 --> 00:06:04,470
And although I was sad that he was gone,

153
00:06:04,470 --> 00:06:07,610
I was also happy because he was free.

